  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason: The proposed extensions by reason of its inappropriate design, scale, massing, and additional bulk would form an overdominant and visually harmful feature when viewed from the rear of 1 & 2 Islington Park Mews.  The development would have a material adverse impact on the amenity of adjoining residents in terms of an increased sense of enclosure, overshadowing, loss of outlook and daylight and sunlight.  The development is therefore considered to be contrary to policy 9 of Islington’s Core Strategy 2011, policies D3 (Site layout), D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and extensions), Islington’s Urban Design Guidance 2006 and planning standard guidelines 2002."
